    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="885"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d885">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.11101 Waivers 81—</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 805</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-02">July 2,
                            1935</date>.<lb/>[Received July 15.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Embassy’s despatch No. 675
                    of February 27th last, I have the honor to report that upon the receipt of a
                    copy of Mr. Blake’s despatch to the Department, No. 1070 of June 17th,<note
                        n="35" xml:id="d885fn1">Not printed.</note> entitled “Discriminatory
                    Passport Regulations in Spanish Zone of Morocco”, I took up this discrimination
                    again with the Foreign Office and have received a Note, dated July 1,<note
                        n="35" xml:id="d885fn2">Not printed.</note> in reply to my representations,
                    a copy and translation of which are enclosed herewith. This Note states that
                    instructions have been sent to the Spanish Consul General in Tangier in order
                    that the presentation of two photographs by American tourists desiring a visa
                    may be no longer necessary.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hallett Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
